# This is an example environment file for the frontend.
# Copy this to .env.local for your local development and customize as needed.
# Variables prefixed with NEXT_PUBLIC_ are exposed to the browser.

# Base URL for the FastAPI backend API.
# This is used by the apiClient.ts to make requests to your backend.
# For local development, if your FastAPI backend runs on port 8000:
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000

# Example for a deployed backend:
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=https://your-production-backend-api.com

# Other frontend-specific example environment variables could go here.
# For example, if you were using a third-party service with a public key:
# NEXT_PUBLIC_THIRD_PARTY_ANALYTICS_KEY=your_public_key_here
